  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This really threw me for a loop and took me a while to track down.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `v1.8.0` and `v1.8.1`\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nYou should be able to set `HTTPVirtualHosts` in your config file without setting the `--rpcvhosts` flag and it should use the virtual hosts defined in the config file.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nSince `RPCVirtualHosts` is `localhost` by default ([as seen here](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/cmd/utils/flags.go#L400-L403)) any virtual hosts defined in the config file are always overridden by `localhost` [here](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/cmd/utils/flags.go#L699)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nIn your config file define `HTTPVirtualHosts = [\"*\"]` and run geth without the `--rpcvhosts` flag. You won't be able to hit your geth node over RPC from anywhere except localhost and you will see this in your logs:\r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO [02-20|02:29:38] HTTP endpoint opened                     url=http://0.0.0.0:8545 cors=* vhosts=localhost\r\nINFO [02-20|02:29:38] IPC endpoint opened                      url=/home/ethereum/data/geth.ipc\r\n```\r\n",
